Description: Part of a jar-seal: of dark brown clay, bearing an impressed inscription of the official Saka, together with a group of signs. The seal has been rolled across the clay twice, producing two impressions at right angles to each other, but only one inscription shows clearly. The surface of the clay is slightly friable.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXI, 28; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.34, abb.104; see also vols. I, 92 and II, 751, n. 477; 1107.
